uk.ac.ebi.mdk.domain.tool
Class PrefixCompartmentResolver

java.lang.Object
  uk.ac.ebi.mdk.domain.tool.PrefixCompartmentResolver
All Implemented Interfaces:
CompartmentResolver
public class PrefixCompartmentResolver
extends Object
implements CompartmentResolver

Provides suggestions for the provided compartment ranked by the levenshtein distance.

Example usage: 

AutomaticCompartmentResolver resolver = new AutomaticCompartmentResolver();
 for(String name : Arrays.asList("c", "g", "e", "a")){
     if(resolver.canResolve(name)){
         System.out.println(resolver.getCompartment(name).getDescription());
     } else {
         System.err.println("Could not resolve compartment: " + name);
     }
 }

Method Detail

addCompartment

public void addCompartment(Compartment compartment)
Adds a compartment to the resolver as three possible keys 1) abbreviation, 2) description and 3) abbreviation surrounded by '[...]'. For example the compartment Cytoplasm will be added to the resolver with the following keys: 'c', 'cytoplasm', and '[c]'. The keys are normalised to lower case by default

Parameters:
compartment - the compartment to add

put

public void put(String key,
                Compartment compartment)
Stores the compartment in a map with the given key. If a compartment with that key already exists then key will stored as ambiguous.

Parameters:
key - key to store
compartment - compartment instance
